			<div class="content" id="post-content-1680984">
									

<p>The containment procedures mention that no one is allowed to tap on the window, and the [DATA EXPUNGED]s in the story of how the window came into the Foundation's possession imply <em>something</em> dramatic happening, but neither of those things are fleshed out, and the article is, as previous comments have agreed, <em>severely</em> underwhelming as a result. All two or three minutes I spent reading this article, I was waiting for at least one of those two points to be elaborated on, and I was very much let down when they weren't.</p>
<p>In short, the idea has some potential - even if it isn't terribly original - but the way it is, as far as I'm concerned, the article fails. Downvoted.</p>

